# Performance Priorities

Optimize for production latency and operational simplicity.

# Rules

* Minimize Bedrock/API calls
* Minimize DB queries
* Avoid unnecessary orchestration
* Avoid unnecessary async jobs
* Avoid fan-out architectures
* Avoid polling when unnecessary
* Avoid unnecessary Turbo broadcasts
* Avoid unnecessary callbacks
* Avoid N+1 queries
* Prefer direct execution paths
* Prefer deterministic Rails logic over additional LLM calls
* Prefer low-query-count solutions
* Optimize hot request paths

# Database

* Prefer pluck/select/exists? when appropriate
* Avoid unnecessary ActiveRecord instantiation
* Avoid callback-heavy flows in latency-sensitive paths

# Async

* Use jobs only for genuinely long-running work
* Keep user-facing request cycles minimal
